Do you have a hobby
Yes, definitely. One of my favorite pastimes is listening to music. Whenever I have some free time, I enjoy immersing myself in my favorite playlist to unwind and disconnect from the hectice pace of daily life.
I find that it really helps me maintain good mental well-being, which is essential for staying focused, and productive at work.

Yes, definitely. One of my favorite pastimes is boxing. It gives me a strong sense of community with fellow boxers, and at the same time, it helps me stay physically active and mentally sharp.

Why do you enjoy it
As I mentioned earlier, I really enjoy it because it helps me clear my mind and disconnect from the hustle and bustle of city life. At the same time, it allows me to stay physicially active and feel more refreshed and focused afterward.

Since I took up boxing, I've lost about four kilograms, which has made me feel much more confident and energized. It's not only improved my physical health but also boosted my confidence when interacting with my friends and peers.

Did you have a hobby as a child
Yes, definitely. I can vividly remember that, as a child, I loved nothing more than playing football with my friends. After being snowed under with schoolwork during the day, spend quality time playing together.
Football is very popular in Vietnam, and many students are big fans of clubs like Liverpool, Manchester City, and indeed Arsenal. So it will always hold a special place in my heart.

What hobbies are popular in your country
In my country, a variety of hobbies are popular, depending on people's lifestyles. For example, many Vietnamese people enjoy social activities like drinking coffee, singing karaoke, and spending quality time with friends.
In big cities like Ho Chi Minh City, it's quite common to see people gathering in the evenings to relax, sing karaoke, or have a few drinks together. These activites are an important part of the social culture.
At the same time, younger people are increasingly interested in hobbies like going to the gym, playing sports, or engaging in online activities such as gaming.

What are the advantages and disadvantages of having a hobby
One main advantage of having a hobby is that it allows people to express their creativity and unwind while enjoying their free time. It can also help reduce stress and improve overall well-being.
On the other hand, a potential disadvantage is that some hobbies can be quite time-consuming and somtimes expensive. For example, a friend of mine enjoys window shopping, but it occassionally turns into actual shopping, which can be costly.

What hobbies would you like to try in the future
I would love to try running a marathon in the future. It might sound a bit ambitious, but I can already imagine the sense of achievement when crossing the finish line and receiving the medal.
Of course, I know it requires a lot of dedication and training, so I'll need to put in the hard work first.
